The Flaw in Trump’s National Security Tariffs Logic
	 	 	 	 CONTENT 
President Donald Trump declared Thursday the U.S. had become too dependent on foreigners for aluminum “that is essential for key military and commercial systems” and slapped a 10% tariff on imports.

If true national security is the goal, then this doesn’t go far enough. You can’t make aluminum without bauxite, yet the U.S. is completely dependent on imports for bauxite; the last domestic mine closed nearly 30 years ago.

